RESIDENCE OF THE PRESIDENT OF THE PHILIPPINES MANILA

PROCLAMATION NO. 329

INCLUDING FROM THE OPERATION OF PROCLAMATION NO. 59, DATED DECEMBER 1, 1926, WHICH ESTABLISHED THE SCHOOL SITE RESERVATION SITUATED IN THE MUNICIPALITY OF ALUBLJID, PROVINCE OF MISAMIS ORIENTAL, A CERTAIN PORTION OF, THE LAND EMBRACED THEREIN, AND RESERVING THE SAME FOR EXPERIMENTAL STATION SITE PURPOSES OF THE PHILIPPINE TOBACCO ADMINISTRATION.

Upon the recommendation of the Secretary of Agriculture and Natural Resources and pursuant to the authority vested in me by law, I, DIOSDADO MACAPAGAL, President of the Philippines, do hereby exclude from the operation of Proclamation No. 59, dated December 1, 1926, which established the school site reservation situated in the Municipality of Alubijid, Province of Misamis Oriental, a certain portion of the land embraced therein and reserve the same for experimental station site purposes under the administration of the Philippine Tobacco Administration, subject to private rights, if any there be, which parcel of land is more particularly described as follows, to wit:

Lot 457-A Csd-8266 (Philippine Tobacco Administration)

“A PARCEL OF LAND (Lot 457-A of the subdivision plan Csd-8266. being, a portion of Lot 457 of plan Gss-580, L.R.C. Record No. _____), situated in the Barrio of Lourdes, Municipality of Alubijid, Province of Misamis Oriental, Bounded on the NE., along line 1-2, by Lot 457-B of the subdivision plan; on the SE., and E., along lines 2-3-4, by Alubijid River; on the SE. and SW., along lines 4-5-6-7, by Lot 190 of Gss-580; and on the NW., along lines 7-8-1, by Municipal Road. Beginning at a point marked “1”‘ on plan, being S. 32.deg. 07’ W., 192.45 m. from B.L.L.M. 1, Gss-580,

268.94 m. to point 2;

186.23 m. to point 3;

148.32 m. to point 4;

133.92 m. to point 5;

128.75 m. to point 6;

186.68 m. to point 7;

324.08 m. to point 8;

110.50 m. to the point of;

beginning containing an area of ONE HUNDRED EIGHTEEN THOUSAND THREE HUNDRED AND NINETY NINE (118,399) Square Meters. All points referred to are indicated on the plan and marked on the ground as follows: points 1 and 2, by B.L. Cyl. Conc. Mons.; point 3; by Old Stake; and the rest, by Old B. L. Cyl. Conc. Mons; bearings true; date of the original survey, April 24, 1961 — Feb. 12, 1963, that of the subdivision survey, Sept. 16, 1963 and approved on Aug. 21, 1964.

NOTE: Lot 457-A = Lot 600 of Alubijid Gss-580.”

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, I have hereunto set my hand and caused the seal of the Republic of the Philippines to be affixed.

Done in the City of Manila, this 24th day of November, in the year of Our Lord, nineteen hundred and sixty-four.

(SGD.) DIOSDADO MACAPAGAL President of the Philippines

By the President:

(SGD.) JUAN S. CANCIO Acting Assistant Executive Secretary

